OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FThe detective in charge of the inquiry
OL,8,Finto the Nottingham attacks has
OL,9,Fapologised to bereaved families for a
OL,10,Fdecision not to take a hair sample to
OL,11,Ftest Valdo Calocane for possible drug
OL,12,Fuse.
OL,14,FDetective Superintendent Leigh
OL,15,FSanders, who has now retired, but was
OL,16,Fthe senior investigating officer for
OL,17,Fthe triple killing and the attempted
OL,18,Fmurder of three van attack victims,
OL,19,Ftold a public inquiry that he believed
OL,20,FCalocane had acted "in cold blood".
OL,26,@|D@TOU|D@bO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FGiving evidence to the inquiry on
OL,8,FWednesday, Mr Sanders, the former head
OL,9,Fof the East Midlands Special
OL,10,FOperations Unit, said he had used the
OL,11,Fword "murder" in documentation in the
OL,12,Faftermath of the June 2023 attacks.
OL,14,FThe inquiry has heard how Calocane, a
OL,15,Fformer mechanical engineering student,
OL,16,Ffatally stabbed University of
OL,17,FNottingham undergraduates Barnaby
OL,18,FWebber and Grace O'Malley-Kumar, both
OL,19,F19, in Ilkeston Road, Nottingham, in
OL,20,Fthe early hours of June 13, 2023.
OL,26,@sD@FOUsD@MO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FHe went on to kill grandfather Ian
OL,8,FCoates, 65, in the Mapperley Park area
OL,9,Faround an hour later, stealing his van
OL,10,Fand using it to run over pedestrians
OL,11,Fat two locations in Nottingham city
OL,12,Fcentre.
OL,14,FCalocane, who admitted manslaughter
OL,15,Fand attempted murder, is detained
OL,16,Findefinitely in a high-security
OL,17,Fhospital after prosecutors accepted
OL,18,Fhis not guilty pleas to murder on the
OL,19,Fgrounds of diminished responsibility
OL,20,Fin January 2024.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FAnswering questions from counsel to
OL,8,Fthe inquiry Rachel Langdale KC, Mr
OL,9,FSanders was asked why he had used the
OL,10,Fterm murderer in regard to Calocane.
OL,12,FThe retired officer said: "My belief
OL,13,Fwas based on the investigations that
OL,14,Fwe had undertaken in relation to VC.
OL,16,F"For me there were elements of
OL,17,Fplanning in relation the killings. My
OL,18,Fview at that time was he didn't seem
OL,19,Fto be under duress.
OL,26,@tD@[OUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,F"He appeared to be making rational
OL,8,Fchoices. My impression was that he was
OL,9,Facting of his own free will.
OL,11,F"As an operational police officer my
OL,12,Fview at that time was that I believed
OL,13,Fhe had murdered in cold blood three
OL,14,Fpeople."
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUvD@HO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FDuring questioning about the issue of
OL,8,Fdiminished responsibility and its
OL,9,Flinks to a police evidence recovery
OL,10,Fplan, it was put to Mr Sanders that
OL,11,Ftoxicology samples had not been taken
OL,12,Fbecause of a lack of consent from
OL,13,FCalocane.
OL,15,FAfter being questioned about an email
OL,16,Fwhich said a hair sample was not taken
OL,17,Ffrom Calocane "as the defendant had no
OL,18,Fhistory" of drug abuse, Mr Sanders
OL,19,Ftold the inquiry: "I have apologised
OL,20,Fin my statement for that.
OL,26,@yD@OOUzD@HO]{D@SOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,F"In hindsight perhaps I should have
OL,8,Fobtained a copy of head hair whilst he
OL,9,Fwas in custody because to do so would
OL,10,Fat least have alleviated some of the
OL,11,Ffears of the families...in relation to
OL,12,Fwhat could have happened in relation
OL,13,Fto the negation of the possible
OL,14,Fdefence of diminished responsibility."
OL,16,FAsked what the value of a hair sample
OL,17,Fcould have been, Mr Sanders said he
OL,18,Funderstood that a sample showing the
OL,19,Fpresence of drugs could have provided
OL,20,Frebuttal for the concept of diminished
OL,21,Fresponsibility.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@fO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1773936670
OL,3,CNottingham attacks detective
OL,4,Capologises to families for not taking
OL,5,Chair sample
OL,7,FBut the ex-officer added that a sample
OL,8,Fof hair "would not be able to provide
OL,9,Fanalysis that showed drugs or alcohol
OL,10,Fin the system at a specific time or
OL,11,Fdate".
OL,13,FCalocane had deceived health
OL,14,Fprofessionals, Mr Sanders said, adding
OL,15,Fof the decision relating to a hair
OL,16,Fsample: "I apologise that we didn't do
OL,17,Fit."
OL,26,@pD@IOUsD@EO]xD@IOUyD@DO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/9
